radiographic_examinations.findings: Low lung volumes and patchy bibasilar opacities.

radiographic_examinations.procedure_name: CT scan of the abdomen and pelvis
radiographic_examinations.findings: A cystic structure (maximum diameter, 8.8 cm) with an asymmetrically thickened and enhancing wall in the pelvis, associated with the right adnexa. A similar peripherally enhancing cystic structure (maximum diameter, 4.3 cm) associated with the left adnexa. Extensive retroperitoneal lymphadenopathy, ascites, and mild, diffuse thickening of multiple bowel loops.
